Who Made The Pride Flag Queer History shorts Welcome to Queer History Part We all know the rainbow flag as the symbol of the LGBTQ plus community But why The rainbow flag was created in by artist veteran and drag performer Gilbert Baker He was commissioned to create a flag for San Diego s Pride Parade by another gay icon politician Harvey Milk The different colours in the flag are intended to represent togetherness since LGBTQ plus people come in all races ages and genders And rainbows are both natural and beautiful The original flag featured eight colors each having a different meaning Hot pink for sex red for life orange for healing yellow for sunlight green for nature turquoise for art indigo for harmony violet for spirit Some flags added black and brown stripes to honor black and brown members of the community A recent update is the progress flag which features the chevron to the side of the original flag to honor trans as well as black and brown community members

harpy eagle animal wildlife nature creatures animalfact habitats amazingfact short zoo The majestic world of the harpy eagle This bird among the largest and most powerful eagles reigns over its kingdom from the treetops With a wingspan of over two meters it commands the skies with grace and precision Renowned for their strength harpy eagles can snatch up prey weighing up to half their body weight Monkeys sloths and other tree dwelling creatures often fall victim to their powerful talons Yet they are not mindless predators Harpy Eagles are devoted parents nurturing their young for nearly two years before they venture off on their own Despite their awe inspiring presence Harpy Eagles are facing threats Deforestation and hunting have dramatically dwindled their numbers placing them on the list of near threatened species But hope is not lost Conservation efforts are underway striving to protect and preserve the habitats of these magnificent birds birds
